accurate|<inform> inform ( > )|Spectral centroid physicalattribute SCM is the weighted average magnitude for a given subband where the weights are the frequency of each magnitude component in that subband . SCM captures to a first order approximation the distribution of energy in a subband for two arbitrary signals with the same average energy . Due to the weighting function the two signals would each be represented by different SCF and SCM values .
